mediaNotes: Male Lesser Goldfinch recorded on 6-2-21 at 11:38 am, in Thousand Oaks, Ventura, CA.  I was attempting to record a NOMO song when a male LEGO flew right over me, singing in flight.  It made a much better recording than the NOMO, which was a bit far away.  Additional species audible - NOMO, HOFI, and OATI.

Lots of mimicry, including: Northern Cardinal, Wilson’s Warbler, Canyon Towhee, Rufous-crowned Sparrow, Bewick’s Wren, Rock Wren, Ash-throated Flycatcher, Bridled Titmouse, Black-throated Sparrow, Arizona Woodpecker, Phainopepla, flicker sp., Bushtit, House Finch, Curve-billed Thrasher, Dark-eyed Junco, Hermit Thrush, Lawrence’s Goldfinch, Woodhouse’s Scrub-Jay, Western Tanager, Verdin, Pine Siskin
